{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TdyGfnV5p2zLF2J1uheQiq","type":"tool_result","content":"  # 1. Change image from \"{{params.spark_image}}-nonexistent\" to \"{{params.spark_image}}\"\n  # 2. Change serviceAccountName from \"spark-nonexistent\" to \"spark-pi\"\n  # 3. Change memory from \"512\" to \"512Mi\"\n\n  # Fix RBAC - add \"pods\" to resources:\n  kubectl patch role spark-pi-role -n spark-pi --type=json \\\n--\n  spark_image:\n    default: apache/spark:3.5.3\n    description: Container image used for the SparkPi job\n\nnamespace_contract:\n  required_roles: []\n--\n  # spark_image 3.5.1 then 3.5.3). The probe keys on the DESIRED image, not on\n  # \"any Job present\": a Job whose image already matches this stage's tag is\n  # left untouched (idempotent), but a stale-image Job from a prior scheduling\n  # FAILS the probe -> the apply delete+recreates a fresh Job with the correct\n  # image, which the agent then fixes. Without the delete-first the second\n  # scheduling silently inherits the first's spec and the oracle false-fails\n--\n  # P18: render the Job manifest from the spark_image param via envsubst so a\n  # workflow override is solvable. Derive the jar version from the same tag;\n  # whitelist ONLY the two var names in single quotes so envsubst leaves the\n  # in-container $SPARK_LOCAL_IP/$(hostname -i)/$EXIT_CODE runtime refs intact.\n  # The \"-nonexistent\" fault stays on the tag.\n  - name: spark_pi_job\n--\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n spark-pi get job spark-pi -o jsonpath=\\\"{.spec.template.spec.containers[0].image}\\\" 2>/dev/null | grep -qF \\\"${BENCH_PARAM_SPARK_IMAGE:-apache/spark:3.5.3}\\\"'\"\n        timeout_sec: 10","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cce1b7d4-b80e-4baa-a443-499afc744632","uuid":"ad30cfd0-dea8-473f-b854-1f04e8044f88","timestamp":"2026-07-04T00:52:50.555Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"  # 1. Change image from \"{{params.spark_image}}-nonexiste